; Regression test for issue #512: --lots does not work with commodities conversion
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/512
;
; With a C directive linking two commodities (e.g. "C BTC 1 = 1,000,000.00 bit"),
; postings specified in either unit should combine correctly under --lots.
;
; Without the fix, the two postings below displayed as separate balance
; entries --- "1.5 BTC" (unannotated) and "500,000.00 bit {0.01 USD}" ---
; because in_place_reduce() rescaled the amount from BTC to bit but left
; the per-unit lot price unchanged (still 10,000 USD/BTC applied to bits).
; That produced two distinct annotated commodities for the same underlying
; lot, so balance_t could not combine them.
;
; With the fix, in_place_reduce() and in_place_unreduce() adjust the lot
; price inversely to the amount scaling, preserving total cost.  The two
; postings now share the same annotation (bit {0.01 USD}) after reduction
; and combine into 2,000,000 bit, which unreduces at display time to
; 2.0 BTC {10,000.00 USD} [2018/01/23].

D 1,000.00 USD

C BTC 1 = 1,000,000.00 bit

2018-01-23 Buy BTC
    Crypto:BTC                             500000.00 bit @@ 5000 USD
    Exchange

2018-01-23 Buy BTC
    Crypto:BTC                             1.5 BTC @@ 15000 USD
    Exchange

test bal --lots
2.0 BTC {10,000.00 USD} [2018/01/23]  Crypto:BTC
      -20,000.00 USD  Exchange
--------------------
2.0 BTC {10,000.00 USD} [2018/01/23]
      -20,000.00 USD
end test

test --base bal --lots
2,000,000.00 bit {0.01 USD} [2018/01/23]  Crypto:BTC
      -20,000.00 USD  Exchange
--------------------
      -20,000.00 USD
2,000,000.00 bit {0.01 USD} [2018/01/23]
end test

test bal
             2.0 BTC  Crypto:BTC
      -20,000.00 USD  Exchange
--------------------
             2.0 BTC
      -20,000.00 USD
end test
